EasterCalculator - Class in <Unnamed>
The EasterCalculator class exists purely for computing parameters to create or edit the EasterDate class object.

EasterDate - Class in <Unnamed>
The EasterDate class is the base class for creating EasterDate objects.
EasterDate(int, int, int) - Constructor for class EasterDate
Constructs the EasterDate object given the month, day, and year.
EasterDate(int, int) - Constructor for class EasterDate
Overload constructor for when an Easter's year is not required.
easterDateIgnoreYear(int) - Static method in class EasterCalculator
The method easterDateIgnoreYear calls the easterFinder method but returns an object only containing an Easter's day and month.
easterFinder(int) - Static method in class EasterCalculator
This method implements the Meeus/Jones/Butcher algorithm in order to compute the date and month of Easter when given the year.
